<OUTPUT_TEXT>
MEMO

To: All Business Intelligence Stakeholders
From: Senior BI Analyst
Subject: Updates on BI Tools, Reports, and Metadata Enhancements

Dear Colleagues,

I am pleased to share the following updates regarding our Business Intelligence infrastructure:

1. New BI Tool Implementation:
   - We have successfully integrated Tableau into our BI ecosystem.
   - Training sessions will be held next week; please check your email for schedule details.

2. Enhanced Reporting Capabilities:
   - The Sales Performance Dashboard now includes real-time data integration.
   - A new Customer Segmentation Report is available in the Shared Reports folder.

3. Metadata Improvements:
   - We've updated our data dictionary to include new fields from the CRM system.
   - Implemented new data lineage tracking for improved data governance.

4. Upcoming Changes:
   - Next month, we'll be rolling out predictive analytics features in our main BI platform.
   - The legacy reporting system will be phased out by Q4; please migrate any critical reports.

For any questions or support, please contact the BI team at bi.support@company.com.

Best regards,
Senior BI Analyst
</OUTPUT_TEXT>
